HEADWORD: Consubstantiality
<hw>Con`sub*stan"ti*al"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?; 106)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Cf. F. <ets>consubstantialit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Participation of the same nature; coexistence in the same
substance.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧His [the Son's] . . .
<xex>consubstantiality</xex> with the Father.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Hammend.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
